"""Base64-embedded static assets.

Why embedded instead of served from /public: Vercel's @vercel/python
builder only bundles files it can statically trace as Python imports/
requirements - it does NOT auto-include arbitrary files read from disk at
runtime (e.g. via Path(...).read_bytes()). A /public folder with no
static-file pipeline wired up (this project uses a single serverless
function + rewrites, not a static build step) silently never makes it
into the deployed bundle - which is why the corner logo 404d/didn't
show up in production even though it worked when tested locally against
the full repo checkout. Embedding the logo as a base64 string literal
inside a .py module sidesteps this entirely, since .py source files are
always included - they are the actual import graph.

Background removed via flood-fill from the border inward (not a flat
color-key threshold), so the black facial outline linework - which is
not connected to the outer background - stays intact while the
surrounding black canvas becomes transparent. Regenerated 2026-07-17
after the source logo image was intentionally replaced.
"""

